OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Work has begun to restore London       
OL,6, Waterloo railway station's 100-year-old
OL,7, glazed roof.                           
OL,9,FWork is needed to replace glass panels 
OL,10,Fand support structures in the roof,    
OL,11,Fwhich was rebuilt just after the First 
OL,12,FWorld War in 1922, Network Rail said.  
OL,14,FAbout 10,000 new glazed panels will be 
OL,15,Finstalled across 12,000 sq m of roof,  
OL,16,Fan area almost twice the size of the   
OL,17,FWembley Stadium pitch.                 
OL,19,FThe new panels roof are to be made from
OL,20,Fa type of plastic, rather than glass.  
